<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,1726,2003]" pageId="22" pageNumber="521">
The newly defined subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="Fery, 2017" authorityName="Fery" authorityYear="2017" box="[497,600,1727,1750]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Hygrotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="521" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto" status="s. str.">
<emphasis box="[497,600,1727,1750]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="521">Hygrotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[612,675,1727,1750]" pageId="22" pageNumber="521" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
includes siX species previously included in the former subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="Fery, 2017" authorityName="Fery" authorityYear="2017" box="[151,254,1764,1787]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Hygrotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="521" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto" status="s. str.">
<emphasis box="[151,254,1764,1787]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="521">Hygrotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[261,323,1763,1786]" pageId="22" pageNumber="521" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, the single species of former genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guignot" authorityYear="1950" box="[726,843,1764,1787]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Heroceras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="521" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[726,843,1764,1787]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="521">Heroceras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peschet" authorityYear="1923" box="[860,1068,1762,1787]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Herophydrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="521" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="descarpentriesi">
<emphasis box="[860,1068,1762,1787]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="521">H. descarpentriesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and all 44 species (one of them bitypic) of the former genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sharp" authorityYear="1880" box="[472,619,1798,1823]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Herophydrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="521" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[472,619,1798,1823]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="521">Herophydrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<figureCitation box="[678,743,1798,1823]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1941,1963]" captionTargetBox="[208,1378,197,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[189,1396,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 2. Dendrogram showing the new classification of Hygrotini. A number of species without molecular data (no voucher number) have been inserted near morphologically similar species with molecular data. Acronyms refer to biogeographical regions." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/884770/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="521">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
and 
<tableCitation box="[797,879,1798,1823]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="5.[125,200,512,532]" captionText="TABLE 1. Checklist of all 137 species of Hygrotini with original, new and former (Nilsson &amp; Há ek 2017 a) generic and subgeneric names; last three columns indicating new combinations, distribution and methods applied to material studied. See Villastrigo et al. (in press) for details on the specimens used in the molecular phylogeny and accession numbers of the sequences." pageId="22" pageNumber="521">Table 1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
