<figureCitation box="[1200,1279,1906,1931]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 18" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1903,1925]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,207,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,193,1882]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 18. Habitus of: (13) Hygrotus (Leptolambus) impressopunctatus, (14) H. (Leptolambus) orthogrammus, (15) H. (Leptolambus) obscureplagiatus, (16) H. (s. str.) guineensis, (17) H. (s. str.) descarpentriesi (male syntype and labels) and (18) H. (Hyphoporus) solieri (Figs 14 and 18 are reproduced from Fery et al. 2012 with the permission of F. Gusenleitner, Linz, Austria)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/884778/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="521">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Aube" baseAuthorityYear="1838" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Herophydrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="521" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guineensis">
<emphasis box="[1325,1353,1908,1931]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="521">H.</emphasis>
(s. str.) 
<emphasis box="[151,269,1943,1966]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="521">guineensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Head of species of former 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fery" authorityYear="2017" box="[597,700,1943,1966]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Hygrotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="521" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[597,700,1943,1966]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="521">Hygrotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with anterior clypeal margin evenly and semicircularly rounded, border produced forwards and with complete bead (see 
<figureCitation box="[773,938,1978,2003]" captionStart="FIGURES 41 – 48" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1912,1934]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[151,1436,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 41 – 48. Head with details of clypeal rim of (41) Hygrotus (Leptolambus) impressopunctatus, (42) H. (Hyphoporus) solieri, (43) H. (s. str.) guineensis, (44) H. (s. str.) inaequalis, (45) idem in lateral view, (46) H. (Coelambus) confluens (the lighter area before the anterior border of the clypeus is the &quot; clypeal stripe &quot;; see Appendix), (47) H. (Leptolambus) masculinus and (48) idem in lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/884784/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="521">Figs 44 and 45</figureCitation>
for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1777" box="[984,1217,1978,2003]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Dytiscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="521" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inaequalis">
<emphasis box="[984,1012,1980,2003]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="521">H.</emphasis>
(s. str.) 
<emphasis box="[1101,1217,1978,2003]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="521">inaequalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); species of former 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sharp" authorityYear="1880" box="[151,298,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Herophydrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,298,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">Herophydrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guignot" authorityYear="1950" box="[360,477,153,176]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Heroceras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[360,477,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">Heroceras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with anterior clypeal margin truncate, straight or slightly emarginated, border not produced forwards; bead present, but in many species narrowed in medial part (see 
<figureCitation box="[1168,1253,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 41 – 48" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1912,1934]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[151,1436,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 41 – 48. Head with details of clypeal rim of (41) Hygrotus (Leptolambus) impressopunctatus, (42) H. (Hyphoporus) solieri, (43) H. (s. str.) guineensis, (44) H. (s. str.) inaequalis, (45) idem in lateral view, (46) H. (Coelambus) confluens (the lighter area before the anterior border of the clypeus is the &quot; clypeal stripe &quot;; see Appendix), (47) H. (Leptolambus) masculinus and (48) idem in lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/884784/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">Fig. 43</figureCitation>
for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Aube" baseAuthorityYear="1838" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Herophydrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guineensis">
<emphasis box="[1312,1340,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">H.</emphasis>
(s. str.) 
<emphasis box="[151,269,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">guineensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), in others medially obsolete or widely reduced eXcept before eyes (cf. AppendiX). Antennomeres simple, not broadened eXcept in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peschet" authorityYear="1923" box="[515,806,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Herophydrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="descarpentriesi">
<emphasis box="[515,543,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">H.</emphasis>
(s. str.) 
<emphasis box="[634,806,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">descarpentriesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with antennomeres of both seXes, but especially males, strongly dilated (
<figureCitation box="[343,428,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 18" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1903,1925]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,207,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,193,1882]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 18. Habitus of: (13) Hygrotus (Leptolambus) impressopunctatus, (14) H. (Leptolambus) orthogrammus, (15) H. (Leptolambus) obscureplagiatus, (16) H. (s. str.) guineensis, (17) H. (s. str.) descarpentriesi (male syntype and labels) and (18) H. (Hyphoporus) solieri (Figs 14 and 18 are reproduced from Fery et al. 2012 with the permission of F. Gusenleitner, Linz, Austria)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/884778/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
). Elytra with margin in lateral view rather strongly ascending to shoulder (similar to 
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 49 – 55" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1345,1367]" captionTargetBox="[191,1436,208,1316]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,193,1323]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 49 – 55. (49 – 53): Epipleuron with oblique epipleural carina and genicular fossa of: (49) Clemnius (s. str.) berneri, (50) Hygrotus (Leptolambus) polonicus polonicus, (51) H. (Coelambus) caspius, (52) H. (Leptolambus) impressopunctatus and (53) Rhithrodytes agnus; epipleural carina (c) and inner margin of epipleuron (m) including angle mentioned in diagnoses of subgenera. (54 – 55): Elytral margin in lateral view of: (54) H. (Coelambus) caspius (strongly ascending to shoulder) and (55) Clemnius (s. str.) berneri (moderately ascending to shoulder) (Figs 52 and 53 are reproduced from Fery 2013 and from Fery 2016 with the permissions of F. Gusenleitner, Linz, Austria, and G. Foster, Ayr, UK, respectively)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/884786/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">Fig. 54</figureCitation>
); epipleuron comparably broad, broader than mesotibia distally; carina meeting inner margin of epipleuron forming a comparably small angle (&lt;ca. 135°; similar to 
<figureCitation box="[847,936,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 49 – 55" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1345,1367]" captionTargetBox="[191,1436,208,1316]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,193,1323]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 49 – 55. (49 – 53): Epipleuron with oblique epipleural carina and genicular fossa of: (49) Clemnius (s. str.) berneri, (50) Hygrotus (Leptolambus) polonicus polonicus, (51) H. (Coelambus) caspius, (52) H. (Leptolambus) impressopunctatus and (53) Rhithrodytes agnus; epipleural carina (c) and inner margin of epipleuron (m) including angle mentioned in diagnoses of subgenera. (54 – 55): Elytral margin in lateral view of: (54) H. (Coelambus) caspius (strongly ascending to shoulder) and (55) Clemnius (s. str.) berneri (moderately ascending to shoulder) (Figs 52 and 53 are reproduced from Fery 2013 and from Fery 2016 with the permissions of F. Gusenleitner, Linz, Austria, and G. Foster, Ayr, UK, respectively)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/884786/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">Fig. 49</figureCitation>
). Elytral pattern diverse (vittate, dotted or uniform); venter black or brown. Last abdominal ventrite without deep depression.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">
Aedeagus with median lobe robust, distal part very diverse in ventral view, more or less symmetric (see 
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 28" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1527,1549]" captionTargetBox="[158,1432,199,1502]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,193,1506]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 28. Median lobe in ventral and lateral view of: (19) Clemnius (Cyclopius) acaroides, (20) Clemnius (s. str.) berneri, (21) Clemnius (s. str.) decoratus, (22) Hygrotus (s. str.) inaequalis, (23) H. (Coelambus) enneagrammus, (24) H. (Coelambus) confluens, (25) H. (Leptolambus) parallellogrammus, (26) H. (Leptolambus) impressopunctatus, (27) H. (s. str.) guineensis and (28) H. (Hyphoporus) tonkinensis (Fig. 28 is a modified reproduction of figs 3 and 4 in Brancucci &amp; Biström 2013)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/884780/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">Figs 22 and 27</figureCitation>
for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1777" box="[321,567,476,501]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Dytiscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inaequalis">
<emphasis box="[321,349,477,500]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">H.</emphasis>
(s. str.) 
<emphasis box="[450,567,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">inaequalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Aube" baseAuthorityYear="1838" box="[628,874,476,500]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Herophydrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guineensis">
<emphasis box="[628,655,477,500]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">H.</emphasis>
(s. str.) 
<emphasis box="[756,874,477,500]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">guineensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or at most slightly asymmetric in some former 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sharp" authorityYear="1880" box="[151,298,511,536]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Herophydrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,298,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">Herophydrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see figures in 
<bibRefCitation author="Bistrom" box="[476,760,511,536]" pageId="23" pageNumber="522" refString="Bistrom, O. &amp; Nilsson, A. N. (2002) Herophydrus Sharp: cladistic analysis, taxonomic revision of the African species, and world check list (Coleoptera: Dytiscidae). Koleopterologische Rundschau, 72, 15 - 111." type="journal article" year="2002">Biström &amp; Nilsson 2002</bibRefCitation>
); parameres with condylar process generally short, forming an obtuse angle with distal part (see 
<figureCitation box="[580,750,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 29 – 40" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1665,1687]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,221,1637]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[144,1443,193,1643]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 29 – 40. Left paramere of: (29) Clemnius (Cyclopius) acaroides, (30) Clemnius (s. str.) berneri, (31) Clemnius (s. str.) decoratus, (32) Hygrotus (s. str.) inaequalis, (33) H. (Leptolambus) fresnedai, (34) H. (Leptolambus) impressopunctatus, (35) H. (Leptolambus) parallellogrammus, (36) H. (Leptolambus) nubilus, (37) H. (Coelambus) enneagrammus, (38) H. (Coelambus) confluens, (39) H. (s. str.) guineensis and (40) H. (Hyphoporus) tonkinensis (Fig. 40 is a modified reproduction of fig. 5 in Brancucci &amp; Biström 2013)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/884782/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">Fig. 32 and 39</figureCitation>
for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1777" box="[803,1047,548,573]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Dytiscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inaequalis">
<emphasis box="[803,831,549,572]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">H.</emphasis>
(s. str.) 
<emphasis box="[930,1047,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">inaequalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Aube" baseAuthorityYear="1838" box="[1107,1352,548,572]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Herophydrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guineensis">
<emphasis box="[1107,1135,549,572]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">H.</emphasis>
(s. str.) 
<emphasis box="[1234,1352,549,572]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">guineensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Male metatarsal claws of equal length.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="522" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,620,645]" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">Distribution.</emphasis>
Palaearctic, Nearctic, Ethiopian and 
<collectingRegion box="[774,870,620,645]" country="Egypt" name="Ash Sharqiyah" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">Oriental</collectingRegion>
. Species of the former subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fery" authorityYear="2017" box="[1245,1348,621,644]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Hygrotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1245,1348,621,644]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">Hygrotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1777" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Dytiscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inaequalis" subGenus="Hygrotus">
<emphasis box="[1409,1436,621,644]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">H.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[160,263,657,680]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">Hygrotus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[284,401,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">inaequalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group in 
<figureCitation box="[521,592,655,680]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1941,1963]" captionTargetBox="[208,1378,197,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[189,1396,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 2. Dendrogram showing the new classification of Hygrotini. A number of species without molecular data (no voucher number) have been inserted near morphologically similar species with molecular data. Acronyms refer to biogeographical regions." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/884770/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) are distributed in Europe, northern Africa, Asia and northern America (reaching northern 
<collectingRegion box="[376,467,692,717]" country="Mexico" name="Mexico" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">
<collectingCountry box="[376,467,692,717]" name="Mexico" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">MeXico</collectingCountry>
</collectingRegion>
); species of former 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sharp" authorityYear="1880" box="[708,854,692,717]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Herophydrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[708,854,692,717]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">Herophydrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occur mainly in Africa, with five species in the Palaearctic, one (
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Klug" baseAuthorityYear="1834" box="[346,557,728,752]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Herophydrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="musicus">
<emphasis box="[346,374,729,752]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">H.</emphasis>
(s. str.) 
<emphasis box="[467,557,729,752]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">musicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) reaching the 
<collectingRegion box="[720,812,727,752]" country="Egypt" name="Ash Sharqiyah" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">Oriental</collectingRegion>
region and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Guignot, 1952)" authorityName="Fery" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Guignot" baseAuthorityYear="1952" box="[947,1352,727,752]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Hygrotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="morandi">
<emphasis box="[947,967,729,752]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">H</emphasis>
. (s. str.) 
<emphasis box="[1068,1163,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">morandi</emphasis>
(Guignot, 1952)
</taxonomicName>
known from 
<collectingCountry box="[212,327,764,789]" name="Cambodia" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">Cambodia</collectingCountry>
only; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peschet" authorityYear="1923" box="[399,690,764,789]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Herophydrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="descarpentriesi">
<emphasis box="[399,427,765,788]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">H.</emphasis>
(s. str.) 
<emphasis box="[517,690,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">descarpentriesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to mountainous regions in south-eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1279,1417,764,789]" name="Madagascar" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1608130919" collectorName="J. Hajek" country="Czech Republic" location="Prague" pageId="23" pageNumber="522" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Prague" typeStatus="holotype">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,433,799,824]" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">
Main habitat 
<typeStatus box="[363,427,799,824]" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">types</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
The subgenus includes species typical of lentic and lotic freshwater environments; some species can be found in inland mineralised or coastal brackish waters, such as for eXample 
<taxonomicName authority="(Millan et al. 2006)" authorityName="Millan et al." authorityYear="2006" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Herophydrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="musicus">
<emphasis box="[1218,1245,837,860]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">H.</emphasis>
(s. str.) 
<emphasis box="[1346,1436,837,860]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">musicus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Millan" box="[158,364,871,896]" pageId="23" pageNumber="522" refString="Millan, A., Abellan, P., Ribera, I., Sanchez-Fernandez, D. &amp; Velasco, J. (2006) The Hydradephaga of the Segura basin (SE Spain): Twentyfive years studying water beetles (Coleoptera). Memorie della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 85, 137 - 158. https: // doi. org / 10.4081 / memorieSEI. 2006.137" type="journal article" year="2006">
Millán 
<emphasis box="[241,290,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">et al</emphasis>
. 2006
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The latter species can also be found in mineral and thermal spring-pools (pers. communication by 
<collectorName box="[186,281,908,933]" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">J. Hájek</collectorName>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[292,373,909,933]" country="Czech Republic" name="Praha" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">Prague</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[383,566,908,933]" name="Czech Republic" pageId="23" pageNumber="522">Czech Republic</collectingCountry>
). The habitat of most African species of the subgenus is poorly known.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
